transcripts.text: Some new developments tonight involving two undocumented immigrants charged with raping an 11-year-old girl in Montgomery County.
These two suspects, both according to ICE, Salvadoran nationals living in the U.S.  illegally, stand accused of raping an 11-year-old Germantown girl on multiple occasions last year.
Five weeks later, Elridge says he's reconsidering his ice ban.
Elridge's about face comes after Montgomery County police arrested at least six undocumented immigrants on rape and child sex abuse charges in the last month alone.
The big concern is that Montgomery County is basically making itself into a safe haven for a criminal element.
